Business Leadership South Africa has blamed President Jacob Zuma for &#8216;plunging the country into a self-created crisis&#8217;. JOHANNESBURG - Business Leadership South Africa (BLSA) has called President Jacob Zuma's Cabinet reshuffle a &quot;radical transformation sabotage&quot;.The association has blamed Zuma for what it calls plunging the country into a self-created crisis .It views ratings agency Standard &amp; Poor s to downgrade South Africa to junk status as catastrophic.BLSA s deputy chairperson Bonang Mohale says it will probably take the country years to get out of this financial trouble. Which country willingly gets itself into recession at a time when we need to be growing so that we can talk about the redistribution of wealth, not the redistribution of poverty? However, S&amp;P Global says its decision to downgrade South Africa s sovereign credit rating to junk status was not influenced by the sacking of former Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan but rather the instability in the country s political landscape, fiscal slippage and slow growth.Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba maintains that the nation shouldn't believe that changing one individual could have led to this, saying there are a whole range of issues that led to the downgrade.WATCH: New Finance Minister aware of junk status downgrade(Edited by Shimoney Regter)